COMMISSIONER OF INTERNAL REVENUE v. HECO ENVELOPE COMPANY. No. 5152. Circuit Court of Appeals, Seventh Circuit. Feb. 6, 1934. I. N. Nelson, of Chicago, Ill., for respondent. Frank J. Wideman, of Washington, D. C., for petitioner.

Before ALSCIIULER, EVANS, and F1TZIIENRY, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

On motion of counsel for petitioner, counsel for respondent consenting thereto, it is now here ordered and adjudged that this cause he docketed in this court and that the petition for a review of the decision of the United States Board of Tax Appeals, entered on August 14, 1933, be, and the same is hereby, dismissed.
